            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[# Paper Annotator 1.1.1

Critical fix for 1.1.0.

- **Fixed: opening any manuscript failed with "Load failed"** — the packaged engine crashed natively (SIGSEGV) on its first manuscript render because `Intl.Segmenter` is broken inside the pkg-bundled Node runtime: it passes capability checks but dies on the first `.segment()` call. Both engine-side call sites (sentence segmentation and grapheme context windows) now detect the packaged runtime and use their fallback splitters — byte-identical behavior for Chinese/ASCII text.
- The packaged smoke test now probes the manuscript render path (`GET /api/manuscript`) so this class of regression cannot ship again.

This build is notarized and stapled; Gatekeeper accepts it on first launch.

Requirements: Apple silicon Mac running macOS 10.13 or later.
]]></description>
